Since 2017, I’ve received an immense amount of support from you all. Whether you’re encouraging my new fashion choices or complimenting my editing skills. But this year I received so many comments just simply wishing for my overall well being & I’m overwhelmed with gratitude to have your support. I feel cared for. I feel seen. And to know that some of you have grown along side with me all these years is something I cherish deeply. Thank you for reaching out, thank you for watching, thank you for sticking up for me against the haters lol & thank you if you’re just simply HERE but not saying anything. I see you & I feel you. wishing you all a successful & abundant 2024!!! Love you 💗🦭💫

Eye of the storm makes its US debut to the Chrysler museum in VA. Never before seen images of the Beatles when they first visited America in ‘63-‘64 that Paul McCartney photographed himself. These images had never before been developed or printed. Now 60 years later, I’m one of the first to witness them 🥲 what an incredible experience!!They have been my favorite band since middle school, from renting all the CD’s at the library, seeing Paul McCartney by myself in yankee stadium at 15 y/o, having a Beatles themed 16th birthday party then finally seeing Ringo Starr live in 2022. This exhibit really hit home for me ❤️
